<paragraph blockId="12.[168,775,277,469]" pageId="12" pageNumber="663">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[168,330,277,301]" pageId="12" pageNumber="663">Identification.</emphasis>
According to 
<bibRefCitation author="Croat TB &amp; Ortiz OO" box="[504,770,277,301]" pageId="12" pageNumber="663" pagination="134 - 186" refId="ref39775" refString="Croat TB, Ortiz OO (2016) A Reappraisal of the Anthurium cuspida- tum Masters Complex, section Polyneurium (Araceae). Aroideana 39: 134 - 186." type="journal article" year="2016">Croat and Ortiz (2016)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Mast." authorityName="Mast." box="[168,500,311,335]" class="Liliopsida" family="Araceae" genus="Anthurium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Alismatales" pageId="12" pageNumber="663" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="cuspidatum">
<emphasis box="[168,425,311,335]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="663">Anthurium cuspidatum</emphasis>
Mast.
</taxonomicName>
is characterized by its usually terrestrial habit, short internodes, persistent cataphylls as fibers, broadly ovate blades wich drying greenish, six to nine pairs basal veins (one to three free from each other) and purple to dark-purple spadices.
</paragraph>
